# Pinterest Content API Skill

Use the local Pinterest content API running at `http://127.0.0.1:8077`.

Before generating anything, check the server:

```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://127.0.0.1:8077/health" -Method Get
```

Generating costs money. Treat every `/bundle` or `/image` call as a potentially
billable generation call, even if `confirm` is omitted. The API has been observed
to generate images and record spend on bare `/bundle` requests that were expected
to be estimate-only.

Spend guardrails:

- NEVER call `/bundle` or `/image` unless the user has explicitly approved the
  exact run in the current conversation (topic/prompt, number of images, quality,
  and expected maximum spend).
- Do not run multiple quality estimates or generations in parallel.
- Default to `n = 1`, `with_images = $true`, and `image_quality = "low"` unless
  the user explicitly approves a larger run or higher quality.
- If the user asks for cost estimates, explain that this API may charge during
  the request; ask whether they approve a small test generation instead.
- Do not rely on `confirm = $true` as the spend boundary. Use explicit user
  approval before any billable endpoint call as the spend boundary.

Example — ONLY after explicit user approval:

```powershell
$body = @{
  topic = "REPLACE_WITH_TOPIC"
  n = 1
  with_images = $true
  image_quality = "low"
} | ConvertTo-Json

Invoke-RestMethod `
  -Uri "http://127.0.0.1:8077/bundle" `
  -Method Post `
  -ContentType "application/json" `
  -Body $body
```

Rules:

- Do not ask for the OpenAI API key. It is already stored in the API project.
- NEVER call `/bundle` or `/image` until the user has approved the spend-risky
  request in this conversation.
- Keep tests cheap: use `n = 1` and `image_quality = "low"` unless the user asks otherwise.
- Shared `$1/day` cap across ALL chats/folders, enforced via `~/.seo-pipeline/budget.json` + `~/.seo-pipeline/.spend_ledger.json`.
- Return the generated title, description, hashtags, board, image path, and bundle folder path.
- If the API is not reachable, tell the user to start it from `Affiliate pages master`:

```powershell
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts\content_api\cli.py serve
```
